item.title: Endangered primates, 1 alive and 1 dead, found in airport luggage
item.description: One of the tiny animals was dead, while the other was seen cradled in the arms of an officer, softly hooting before covering its face with its arm.

item.title: YouTube TV drops Disney networks after impasse over new agreement
item.description: Disney networks including ABC and ESPN have gone dark on Google-owned YouTube TV after the two corporate giants couldn't come to terms on a new deal.

item.title: U.N. rights chief says "unacceptable" U.S. strikes on boats must stop
item.description: The United Nations human rights chief says the Trump administration "must halt" strikes on alleged drug boats to prevent "extrajudicial killing."

item.title: 2 dead after severe flooding sweeps NYC amid record rainfall
item.description: The National Weather Service reported 1.85 inches in Central Park, breaking the previous daily rainfall record of 1.64 inches set in 1917.

item.title: 9/26: CBS Morning News
item.description: Former FBI Director James Comey indicted; Texas teen confesses to stabbing twin in 911 call.
